{"parse":{"title":"food","pageid":2198,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:fode|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|fode}}, {{m|enm|foode}}, from {{inh|en|ang|fōda||food}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*fōdō}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*fōdô||food}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*peh₂-||to guard, graze, feed}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|sco|fuid||food}}, {{cog|nds|föde}}, {{m|nds|vöde||food}}, {{cog|fy|fiedsel||food}}, {{cog|nl|voedsel||food}} {{cog|da|føde||food}}, {{cog|sv|föda||food}}, {{cog|is|fæða}}, {{m|is|fæði||food}}, {{cog|got|𐍆𐍉𐌳𐌴𐌹𐌽𐍃||food}}, {{cog|la|pānis||bread, food}}, {{cog|la|pāscō||feed, nourish|pos=verb}}. Related to {{l|en|fodder}}, {{l|en|foster}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|fōōd}}, {{IPA|en|/fuːd/}}, {{rhymes|en|uːd|s=1}}\n** {{IPA|en|[fuːd]|[fʊwd]|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|[fu̟(ː)d]|[fʊwd]|a=GA}}\n** {{IPA|en|[fʉwd]|a=SSBE}}\n** {{IPA|en|[fʉːd]|[fyːd]|a=South Africa}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-food.ogg|a=London|IPA=[fɵ̝ʉ̯d]}}\n** {{audio|en|En_US_Food.wav|a=Southern California|IPA=[fʉːd]}}\n** {{audio|en|Fʏːd.wav|a=MLE|IPA=[fʏːd]}}\n* {{enPR|fŏŏd}}, {{rhymes|en|ʊd|s=1}}\n** {{IPA|en|/fʊɖ/|ref={{Cite book|last=Sailaja|first=Pingali|page=27|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ntxWxuoRBiwC|title=Indian English|publisher=Edinburgh University Press|year=2009|isbn=978-0-7486-2595-6|series=Series: Dialects of English}}|a=India}}\n** {{IPA|en|/fʊd/|a=US,dialectal; Ottawa Valley|ref={{R:en:McDavid:1979|13|116}}}}\n* {{homophones|en|FoD}}\n\n===Noun===\n[[File:Good Food Display - NCI Visuals Online.jpg|250px|thumb|Various '''foods''']]\n{{en-noun|-|s}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q2095}}{{lb|en|uncountable}} Any solid [[substance]] that can be consumed by living organisms, especially by [[eat]]ing, in order to sustain life.\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:food}}\n#: {{ux|en|The innkeeper brought them '''food''' and drink.}}\n#* {{RQ:Travers Cuckoo in the Nest|chapter=1|passage=“{{...}} the awfully hearty sort of Christmas cards that people do send to other people that they don't know at all well. You know. The kind that have mottoes like<br>&nbsp; Here's rattling good luck and roaring good cheer, / With lashings of '''food''' and great hogsheads of beer. {{...}}”}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-29|volume=407|issue=8842|page=72–3|magazine=w:The Economist| title=[http://www.economist.com/news/international/science-and-technology/21580133-how-microbes-promote-liver-cancer-overweight-punch-gut A punch in the gut]| passage=Mostly, the microbiome is beneficial. It helps with digestion and enables people to extract a lot more calories from their '''food''' than would otherwise be possible. Research over the past few years, however, has implicated it in diseases from atherosclerosis to asthma to autism.}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A [[foodstuff]], a type of food.\n#: {{syn|en|belly-timber|q1=archaic, now only humorous or regional|foodstuff|provender|Thesaurus:food}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=C Williams; J Buttriss|title=Improving the Fat Content of '''Foods'''|page=492|isbn=1845691075\n|passage=Variation and changes in the trans fatty acid content of different '''foods''', especially in processed '''foods''', further complicate such estimates.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|figuratively}} Anything that nourishes or sustains.\n#: {{hypo|en|brainfood}}\n#: {{ux|en|The man's inspiring speech gave us '''food''' for thought.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Mozart and Bach are '''food''' for my soul.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Much Ado About Nothing|act=I|scene=iii|passage=This may prove '''food''' to my displeasure.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1798|author=w:William Wordsworth|title=[[s:Lyrical Ballads (1798)/Lines written a few miles above Tintern Abbey|Tintern Abbey]]\n|passage=In this moment there is life and '''food''' / For future years.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|MLE}} Any illegal [[substance]] or illegal [[substance]]s, [[drug]]s.\n#* {{quote-song|en|date=2009-03-17|artist=w:Tempa T|album=All-Star Pars|track=3|title=Next Hype|url=https://genius.com/Tempa-t-next-hype-lyrics|passage=What kind of things that you have. When I find out don't expect me to stop. I'll come for the P's that you stack. And come for the '''food''' that you blot.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=2015|author=w:Stormzy|artist=Stormzy|title={{w|Shut Up (Stormzy song)|Shut Up}}|album=w:Gang Signs & Prayer|track=15|passage=I'm so London, I'm so south / '''Food''' in the ends like there ain't no drought / Flipz don't talk like he's got no mouth}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|date=2016-03-04|artist={{w|Kano (British musician)}},{{w|Giggs (rapper)}},{{w|Wiley (musician)}}|album=Made in the Manor|track=4|title=3 '''Wheel-Ups'''|url=https://genius.com/Kano-3-wheel-ups-lyrics|passage=[Verse 2:Kano]:If you've been shotting in the manor from way back when and you ain't on a kilo ting, I don't wanna hear about [[cunch]] and '''food''' and tings, man don't do those tings.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{syn|en|Thesaurus:food}}\n* {{sense|substance consumed by living organisms}} {{l|en|belly-timber}} {{qualifier|archaic, now only humorous or regional}}, [[chow]] {{qualifier|slang}}, [[comestible]] {{qualifier|formal}}, [[eats]] {{qualifier|slang}}, [[feed]] {{qualifier|for domesticated animals}}, [[fodder]] {{qualifier|for domesticated animals}}, [[foodstuff]]s, [[grub]] {{q|informal}}, [[nosh]] {{qualifier|slang}}, [[nourishment]], [[provender]], [[scran]] {{q|dialectal}}, [[sustenance]], [[victuals]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|agri-food\n|ambient food\n|angel food\n|angel-food cake,angel food cake,angel's-food cake,angel's food cake\n|animal food|dry food|food-insecure|food-secure|K-food|wet food\n|antifood\n|avoidant/restrictive food intake disorder\n|baby food\n|bushfood\n|cat food\n|cheese food|milk food\n|Chinese food syndrome\n|cold food powder|food styling|food writer|food writing|food-truck|food-writing\n|comfort food\n|convenience food||ultra-processed food\n|cottage food operation\n|deerfood\n|devil's-food cake,devil's food cake\n|dog food,dogfood\n|dude food\n|eat one's own dog food\n|every good boy deserves food\n|famine food\n|fast-food,fast food|food for the gods\n|fast food music\n|finger food\n|fish food\n|food additive\n|foodaholic\n|food allergy\n|food and board\n|food art\n|food artist\n|food baby|food digger|food steamer\n|food bank\n|food banking|Wikipedia food\n|food-borne\n|foodborne\n|food-borne disease\n|food bowl\n|food cache|food line\n|food canal\n|food cart\n|foodcation\n|food chain\n|food closet\n|food coloring\n|food colouring\n|food coma\n|food court\n|food crop\n|food-derived illness\n|food desert\n|food drive\n|foodery\n|food fall\n|food-fall\n|foodfest\n|food fight\n|food fish\n|foodflation\n|food for powder\n|food for the worms\n|food for thought\n|food for worms\n|food fraud\n|foodful\n|food garden\n|foodgasm\n|food-grade\n|foodgrain\n|food hall\n|foodie\n|food insecurity\n|food intolerance\n|foodious\n|foodism\n|foodist\n|foodista\n|foodlegger\n|foodless\n|foodlike\n|food literacy\n|food-literate\n|foodloaf\n|food miles\n|food mill\n|food mixer\n|foodmonger\n|food noise\n|food oasis\n|foodoir\n|foodomics\n|foodophile\n|food pantry\n|food pipe\n|food plant\n|food play\n|foodplay\n|food poisoning\n|foodporn\n|food porn\n|foodpreneur\n|foodprint\n|food processor\n|food puzzle\n|food pyramid\n|foodscape\n|food science\n|food scientist\n|food security\n|foodseller\n|food service\n|foodservice\n|foodshed\n|food shop\n|food sovereignty\n|foodstagram\n|foodstall\n|food stamp\n|foodstore\n|food street\n|foodstuff\n|foodstyle\n|food stylist\n|food supplement\n|food swamp\n|foodtech\n|food-to-go\n|foodtography\n|FoodTok\n|food tree\n|food trip\n|food truck\n|food vacuole\n|foodware\n|food waste disposer\n|foodway\n|food web\n|foodweb\n|foodwise\n|food wrap\n|foodwriting\n|foody\n|foodyolk\n|frankenfood\n|frozen food\n|functional food\n|ground food\n|hard food\n|health food\n|junk food\n|junk food news\n|larval food plant\n|lawn food\n|multifood\n|nanofood\n|natural food\n|nonfood\n|non-food\n|ou